The Oodua People’s Congress (OPC), Oyo State chapter, has told the former Minister of Aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode, to produce to the whole world, the real Fulani warlord terrorising the people of Ayete, Igangan and Ibarapa areas of Oyo State.  The chapter through the Chairman, Mr. Rotimi Oguntade, popularly called Olumo, said the claims of the former minister that the person arrested by the men of the OPC was not the Iskilu Wakilin was not only untrue, but also misleading. He described Fani-Kayode as a spoiler, an agent of destruction and a political feather weight reputed for changing the narratives and misinforming the public. Olumo said: “Fani-Kayode’s utterances merited no response, but because it came at a time the chief tormentor of Ibarapa people is still in custody, it is reasonable to respond and clear the air on the issue.”  Source The Coordinator of the Oodua Peoples Congress in Oyo State, Mr Rotimi Olumo, has described a former Minister of Aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode, as a ‘lie merchant and an expert in misinformation.’ Olumo said this in a statement on Wednesday following a claim by Fani-Kayode that the Fulani warlord, Abdullah Iskilu-Wakili,… In "News" •The Iskilu Wakili declared fake by Fani-Kayode A septuagenarian arrested by members of the Oodua Peoples Congress (OPC) is not the “wanted Wakili”, according to Former Minister of Aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode.Some members of the OPC in Oyo State had, on Sunday, razed a Fulani settlement at Kajola in Ibarapa area of… In "Top Stories" Former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani-Kayode has revealed that the governorship candidate of the People Democratic Party (PDP) in Lagos State, Jimi Agbaje, has dumped the party. Former Aviation Minister, Femi Fani-Kayode has revealed that the governorship candidate of the People Democratic Party (PDP) in Lagos State, Jimi Agbaje, has dumped… In "Top Stories"